{"parse":{"title":"Mental Health (Care and Treatment) Act (Singapore)","pageid":34255164,"revid":652907063,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Mental Health</b> (Care and Treatment) Act (Singapore)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> was passed in 2008 to regulate the <a href=\"/wiki/Involuntary_commitment\" title=\"Involuntary commitment\">involuntary detention</a> of a person in a <a href=\"/wiki/Psychiatric_institution\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Psychiatric institution\">psychiatric institution</a> for the treatment of a <a href=\"/wiki/Mental_disorder\" title=\"Mental disorder\">mental disorder</a>, or in the interest of the health and safety of the person or the persons around him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Form_1\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Form 1</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Form_2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Form 2</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Form_3\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Form 3</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Form_4\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Form 4</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Form_5\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Form 5</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Form_1\">Form 1</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mental_Health_(Care_and_Treatment)_Act_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Form 1\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Form 1 in the first schedule of the act empowers a designated <a href=\"/wiki/Medical_practitioner\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Medical practitioner\">medical practitioner</a> at a psychiatric institution to admit a person suffering from a mental disorder into the psychiatric institution, and detain the patient for up to 72 hours.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Form_2\">Form 2</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mental_Health_(Care_and_Treatment)_Act_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Form 2\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A patient that has been admitted under Form 1, may be detained for a further period of 1 month after the expiration of the 72-hour period under the provision of Form 2 in the first schedule of the act, if the following requirements are fulfilled:\n</p>\n<ol><li>The patient is examined by another designated medical practitioner at the institution, and is of the opinion that further treatment is needed</li>\n<li>The designated practitioner signs Form 2</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Form_3\">Form 3</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mental_Health_(Care_and_Treatment)_Act_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Form 3\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Form 3 allows for a patient detained under form 2 to be further detained for up to 6 months if:\n</p>\n<ol><li>2 Designated medical practitioners (of which at least one must be a <a href=\"/wiki/Psychiatrist\" title=\"Psychiatrist\">psychiatrist</a>) have examined the patient separately and are satisfied that the patient requires further treatment at the psychiatric institution</li>\n<li>It is necessary in the interest of the health or safety of the person or for the protection of other persons that the person should be detained</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Form_4\">Form 4</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mental_Health_(Care_and_Treatment)_Act_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Form 4\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Form 4 of the Act allows for visitors to apply to a <a href=\"/wiki/Magistrate\" title=\"Magistrate\">Magistrate</a> for Form 5.\nThe visitors are appointed by the Minister of Health. At least 12 visitors are appointed at any time, and at least 6 have to be medical practitioners. 2 or more visitors have to visit the designated psychiatric institution at least once every 3 months.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Form_5\">Form 5</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mental_Health_(Care_and_Treatment)_Act_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Form 5\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Form 5 in the First Schedule of the act is an order made by a Magistrate, which allows for the patient to be detained for a further 12 months.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mental_Health_(Care_and_Treatment)_Act_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.parliament.gov.sg/sites/default/files/080011.pdf\">http://www.parliament.gov.sg/sites/default/files/080011.pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.pap.org.sg/articleview.php?id=3756&amp;cid=84\">http://www.pap.org.sg/articleview.php?id=3756&amp;cid=84</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1240\nCached time: 20180911043549\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.036 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.043 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 120/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 866/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 146/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 803/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.004/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 523 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   26.295      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   26.295      1 -total\n  8.47%    2.227      1 Template:Main_other\n  5.91%    1.555      1 Template:Column-width\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:34255164-0!canonical and timestamp 20180911043549 and revision id 652907063\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":